# S03 — BACKEND_DEV Brief: eWeLink Refinement

role: BACKEND_DEV
sprint: S03
stack: Node.js (ESM), Express, Socket.IO, eWeLink SDK/API

tasks:
  - eWeLink client service (auth, device list, control)
  - REST endpoints: GET /devices/ewelink, POST /devices/:id/control
  - Normalize device payload for frontend (id, type, channels, status, power)
  - Socket.IO emit on device status change
  - Multi-channel switch support in control logic

implementation:
  - Async/await, centralized error handling
  - Dedicated eWeLink service (abstraction for future Tuya)
  - .env for eWeLink credentials
  - Rate limiting / retry for eWeLink API

defer-if-complex:
  - LAN mode (local control) — research, may move to backlog
  - Historical power — only if eWeLink provides API

anti-patterns:
  - Hardcoded credentials
  - Blocking event loop
  - Global mutable state
